[codex] revision-analysis/_r2_review\codex_session.log:1217:[codex] > According to Feedback Intervention Theory, feedback most effectively regulates behavior change when paired with explicit goals, norms or targets that allow recipients to gauge their performance and direct their efforts accordingly (Kluger & DeNisi, 1996, 1998; Locke & Latham, 2019; Itzchakov & Latham, 2018; Chen, Latham, & Piccolo, 2020).
